**3. Every Friday --- Weekly Run Checklist**

  ---------- ------------------------------------------------ -------------
  **Step**   **Action**                                       **Time**

  1          Build this week\'s NMF playlist in Spotify from  15-20 min
             blogs                                            

  2          Export via Exportify → save as data/nmf.csv      2 min

  3          Run 2026 notebook top to bottom (skip wrapping   \~13 min
             paper cells)                                     

  4          Open Streamlit app --- browse predictions, rate  Weekend
             a few albums                                     

  5          Gut score pull runs automatically next Friday at Automatic
             notebook start                                   
  ---------- ------------------------------------------------ -------------

*Tip: Build next week\'s playlist on your work laptop while the model
runs on your personal PC. Nearly zero idle time.*

**4. Catch-Up Run Plan (Jan 1 --- Mar 7)**

You have \~10 weeks of missed NMF to archive for the Hidden Gems
backlog. None of these weeks need perfect predictions --- the goal is
just to populate data/archived_nmf_with_features/ so the Historical
Ratings page has something to browse.

-   **Build each week\'s playlist** from your usual blogs in Spotify

-   **Export via Exportify** → save as data/nmf.csv

-   **Run the notebook.** Each run archives that week automatically.

-   **Repeat \~10 times.** Parallel workflow: build next playlist while
    current run trains.

-   **Speed option:** temporarily drop n_iter=20 to n_iter=10 in Cell 45
    for catch-up runs, restore for weekly runs.

*Important: The date shown in the Streamlit dropdown comes from Release
Date in nmf.csv --- not when you ran the notebook. As long as the tracks
have correct release dates, the app labels each week correctly even if
you ran them all on the same afternoon.*

**5. Architecture --- What Lives Where**

  ----------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------
  **File / Folder**                               **Purpose**

  data/nmf.csv                                    This week\'s NMF tracks from Exportify
                                                  --- swap out every Friday

  data/2026_training_complete_with_features.csv   Master training set --- grows weekly as
                                                  gut scores are added

  data/archived_nmf_with_features/                Full-featured NMF tracks from every
                                                  past week --- feeds Hidden Gems

  data/backups/                                   Auto-backup of training CSV created
                                                  before each Thursday update

  feedback/master_gut_scores.csv                  Every gut score you\'ve ever entered
                                                  --- source of truth

  feedback/{date}\_gut_scores.csv                 Weekly gut score files ---
                                                  automatically merged into master

  predictions/{date}\_Album_Recommendations.csv   Weekly prediction output --- Streamlit
                                                  reads these for the dropdown

  data/nmf_album_covers.csv                       Cumulative album art cache --- grows
                                                  each week

  data/nmf_album_links.csv                        Cumulative Spotify link cache --- grows
                                                  each week

  data/liked_artists_only_similar.csv             Last.fm similar artists --- grows as
                                                  new artists appear

  data/ten_genres.csv                             Genre cache --- Last.fm fetched genres,
                                                  updated each run

  data/obscure_artists_mike_likes.csv             Manual genre overrides for artists
                                                  Last.fm doesn\'t know

  .env                                            API keys --- never commit this file
  ----------------------------------------------- ---------------------------------------

**6. Possible Future Improvements**

**App.py --- Nice to Have**

-   **Hidden Gems cache refresh:** Currently requires manually clicking
    \'Update Hidden Gems Cache\' in sidebar. Could auto-refresh after
    each Thursday pull.

-   **Album art fallback:** When Apple Music returns no art, could try
    MusicBrainz Cover Art Archive as a secondary source.

-   **Spotify link generation:** Cell 61 hits Spotify API and is slow.
    Could be parallelized more aggressively or cached more
    intelligently.

-   **st.cache_data TTL:** load_album_covers() is cached indefinitely.
    After catch-up runs with many new weeks, the cache will serve stale
    art until manually cleared. Consider setting TTL=3600.

**Model --- Possible Upgrades**

-   **apply_confidence_scaling:** Just restored from 2025. Worth
    comparing predicted vs gut score accuracy over the first month to
    see if it\'s actually helping.

-   **gut_score_rated weighting:** Currently gut-scored albums get
    importance_weight applied like any other training row. Could give
    them higher weight since they\'re your most recent, specific signal.

-   **Discovery classifier:** Cell 49 trains a binary 85+ classifier.
    Its output (discovery_chance) isn\'t surfaced in the Streamlit app
    yet --- could be a useful secondary signal.

**Data --- Exportify Dependency**

-   **Exportify is grandfathered:** Pre-November 2024 Spotify API
    access. Don\'t create a new Spotify developer app or modify your
    existing one --- this would lose grandfathered access.

-   **Contingency plan:** If Exportify loses access, Last.fm has
    track-level data and genre tags but no audio features. mood_score
    and energy_profile would need to be rebuilt from genre proxies. Not
    urgent.

**7. Key Files to Bring to Future Sessions**

When starting a new Claude session on this project, upload or reference:

-   **2026_Music_Taste_Machine_Learning_Data_Prep.ipynb** --- the main
    notebook, source of truth for the pipeline

-   **RUN_THURSDAY.ipynb** --- gut score integration (now embedded in
    main notebook, but keep as backup)

-   **streamlit_app.py** --- the Streamlit UI

-   **A short note:** what changed last week, what broke, what you want
    to tackle

*Claude Projects keeps memory of this session context, but uploading the
notebook ensures Claude can read the exact current state of your code
rather than relying on session memory.*

